
TY  - JOUR
T1  - Hypothesis Creation in Organizational Behavior Research
AU  - Lundberg, Craig C.
Y1  - 1976/04/01
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1976.4408646
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1976.4408646
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 5
EP  - 12
VL  - 1
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The field of organizational behavior has begun to place undue emphasis on hypothesis testing and thereby underemphasize hypothesis generation. After suggesting several reasons for this, this paper reviews how useful research ideas are discovered and the prerequisites for hypothesis creation, and then catalogues hypothesis generation. Suggested criteria for acting on new research ideas and questions are: extensity, professional encounter, mental experiments, and timing.
AB  - The field of organizational behavior has begun to place undue emphasis on hypothesis testing and thereby underemphasize hypothesis generation. After suggesting several reasons for this, this paper reviews how useful research ideas are discovered and the prerequisites for hypothesis creation, and then catalogues hypothesis generation. Suggested criteria for acting on new research ideas and questions are: extensity, professional encounter, mental experiments, and timing.
